description:
In 2014, brothers Ade and Judah brought their previous band of 11 years, &quot;Cocaine Cowboys&quot;, back from the ashes and rising like a phoenix as a new band, &quot;The Devil's Disciples&quot;. To complete the new line up, they've added EJ, a bassist with a punk background and three years experience with a Sex Pistols cover band who follow Sick Mohawk and the hard core punk of The A-Cab. So in 2014, the line up of &quot;The Devil's Disciples&quot; is: Ade on lead guitar and vocals, Judah on drums and EJ on bass. Their various tastes and influences have found common ground in the style forged by Motorhead and Venom. Without any pretence of revolutionising genres or creating something new, but simply wanting to be themselves, they wrote their first few songs which they recorded in October with sound engineer Federico Viola, in Animal House Studio, Ferrara. They released their first self-produced cd called, &quot;In the Name of Hell&quot;.

In 2015 June E.J. left the band and Raven take the role of bass player.

TRACKLIST:
01. Church Burner
02. Rotten
03. Worshippers Of The Dying Whore
04. Lucifer
05. School Of The Devil
06. The Devil Ain't Dwells In Hell
07. Edge Of Insanity
08. See you In Hell

